data.name: ZoomPolicy_AR_ActiveReports
data.value: Viewer is ActiveReports’s content control, its content area can’t zoom, ActiveReportsZoomPolicy ensure anywhere in Viewer can zoom.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_C1_C1Calendar
data.value: C1CalendarZoomPolicy supports C1Calendar’s zooming behavior, when you zoom C1Calendar, the C1CalendarZoomPolicy can give you the best zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_C1_C1Chart
data.value: C1ChartZoomPolicy provides ability to change special properties of C1Chart, such as the following. Font Size ChartLabel ChartArea Axis PlotArea So that, you can get the best zoom result when zoom C1Chart by C1ChartZoomPolicy.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_C1_C1Chart3D
data.value: C1Chart3DZoomPolicy provides ability to support C1Chart3D’s zooming behavior that you can get the best zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_C1_C1DockingTab
data.value: If you change Font or Size property's default value of C1DockingTab, you can get the best zoom result by using C1DockingTabZoomPolicy.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_C1_C1FlexGrid
data.value: If you change C1FlexGrid.Colunm.Width, C1FlexGrid.Row.Height, C1FlexGrid.Font, and C1FlexGrid.Size value, add C1FlexGridZoomPolicy in your application can help you get a better zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_C1_C1NavBar
data.value: C1NavBarZoomPolicy provides ability to support C1NavBar’s zooming behavior.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_C1_C1OutBar
data.value: If you change Font or Size property's default value of C1OutBar, you can get the best zoom result by using C1OutBarZoomPolicy.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_C1_C1PrintPreviewControl
data.value: If you change C1PrintPreviewControl.Font value, add C1ReportZoomPolicy can make sure that every elements in C1PrintPreviewControl will zoom correctly.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_C1_C1Ribbon
data.value: When you do zoom operation, C1Ribbon’s Font can be zoom, but Size can’t be zoom. So C1Ribbon’s Font can’t be shown completely after zoom. MultiTouch for Windows Forms provides C1RibbonZoomPolicy to make sure that C1Ribbon’s Font and Size don’t change, they always display original Font and Size.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_C1_C1Schedule
data.value: C1ScheduleZoomPolicy supports C1Schedule’s zooming behavior, when you zoom C1Schedule, the C1ScheduleZoomPolicy can give you the best zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_C1_C1StatusBar
data.value: When you do zoom operation, C1StatusBar’s Font can be zoom, but Size can’t be zoom. So C1StatusBar’s Font can’t be shown completely after zoom. MultiTouch for Windows Forms provides C1StatusBarZoomPolicy to make sure that C1StatusBar’s Font and Size don’t change, they always display original Font and Size.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_C1_C1TrueDBGrid
data.value: C1TrueDBGridZoomPolicy changes C1TrueDBGrid.CellTipsWidth, C1TrueDBGrid.DefColWidth, C1TrueDBGrid.RecordSelectorWidth, or some other properties value, so you can get the best zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_IM_GcCharMask
data.value: GcCharMaskZoomPolicy make sure that you can get the best zoom result when you change GcCharMask.CharBoxes.Size, GcCharMask.CharBoxSpacing, GcCharMask.CharBoxes.Font value.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_IM_GcComboBox
data.value: You may change GcComboBox.SideButtons.ButtonWidth, GcComboBox.DropDownMaxHeight, GcComboBox.DropDown.Size value, in order to get the best zoom result, you need add GcComboBoxZoomPolicy in your application.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_IM_GcDateTime
data.value: MultiTouch Toolkit provides GcDateTimeZoomPolicy so that you can get the best zoom result when you change GcDateTime.DropDownCalendar.Font value.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_IM_GcListBox
data.value: If GcListBox.ItemTemplates.AutoItemHeihgt value is False and GcListBox.ItemTemplates.Height value changed, add GcListBoxZoomPolicy can help you get the best zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_IM_GcMask
data.value: GcMaskZoomPolicy can help you get the best zoom result when you change GcMask.SideButtons.ButtonWidth, GcMask.SideButtons.DropDown.Size, GcMask.SideButtons.MaskPatternField.Font value.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_IM_GcNumber
data.value: Change some propeties value, such as GcNumber.DisplayFields[i].Font GcNumber.DropDownCalculator.OutputHeight GcNumber.Fields[i].Font GcNumber.SideButtons[i].ButtonWidth GcNumber.PopUpCalculator.Font and so on, may cause zoom result error, you can get a better zoom result by using GcNumberZoomPolicy.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_IM_GcTextBox
data.value: MultiTouch for Windows Forms provides GcTextBoxZoomPolicy, the policy can help you get the best zoom result when you set GcTextBox.MultiLine value is True and change GcTextBox.DropDownEditor.Font value.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_IM_GcTimeSpan
data.value: GcTimeSpan’s following properties can’t be zoom, you can add GcTimeSpanZoomPolicy to make sure that all elements in GcTimeSpan can be zoom. GcTimeSpan.SideButtons[i].ButtonWidth GcTimeSpan.Fields[i].Font GcTimeSpan.DisplayFields[i].Font

data.name: ZoomPolicy_LT_RasterImageList
data.value: RasterImageListZoomPolicy make sure every images could be zoomed when you zooming.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_LT_RasterImageViewer
data.value: RasterImageViewerZoomPolicy change the RasterImageViewer.ScaleFactor to get a better zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcAccordionContainer
data.value: If GcAccordionContainer.ItemSpace and GcAccordionContainer.HeaderSettings.Font changed, you can add GcAccordionContainerPolicy to get the best zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcBarCode
data.value: If GcBarCode.AdjustSize value is False, GcBarCodeZoomPolicy moves GcBarCode to the center of the blank space.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcCalculator
data.value: If you set GcCalculator.ShowOutput value is True and GcCalculator.OutputHeight value is bigger than 0, GcCalculatorZoomPolicy can help you to get a better zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcCalendar
data.value: If you change some properties value as below, such as GcCalendar.HeaderHeight GcCalendar.InnerSpace GcCalendar.NavigatorButtonSize GcCalendar.DefaultNoteStyle.ImageSize GcCalendar.ControlStyle.Font GcCalendar.TitleStyle.Font GcCalendar.WeekNumberStyle.Font and so on, PlusPakCalendarZoomPolicy can make sure that you will get a better zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcCheckBox
data.value: GcCheckBoxZoomPolicy will give you the best zoom result when you set GcCheckBox.CheckMarkAutoSize value is False and change GcCheckBox.CheckMarkSize value.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcClassicFunctionKey
data.value: If you set GcClassicFunctionKey.ButtonWidth, or ButtonHeight, or ColumnSpacing, or GroupSpacing, or RowSpacing, you can get the best zoom result by using GcClassicFunctionKeyZoomPolicy.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcComboFrame
data.value: If you set GcComboFrame.DropDownSettings.AutoSize value is False and change GcComboFrame.DropDownSettings.Size value, you can add GcComboFrameZoomPolicy to get a better zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcContainer
data.value: When GcContainer.ApplyCaptionFormat property is All, you change GcContainer.CaptionFormat.Size, GcContainer.CaptionFormat.Spacing, GcContainer.CaptionFormat.Font value, or when GcContainer.ApplyCaptionFormat is Individual, you change Controls[i].CaptionFormat.Size, Controls[i].CaptionFormat.Size, Controls[i].CaptionFormat.Font value, GcContainerPolicy is able to help you get the best zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcDropDownButton
data.value: If GcDropDownButton.DropDown isn’t null, when you zoom, DropDown’s Font can’t zoom as DropDownButton’s Font. GcDropDownButtonZoomPolicy can help you solve this issue.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcFlowLayoutContainer
data.value: After zoom, GcFlowLayoutContainer’s layout may uncorrectly when you set CaptionText to the children, you can get a better zoom result by using GcFlowLayoutContainerZoomPolicy.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcFontPicker
data.value: If you set GcFontPicker.DropDownSettings.Size, ItemStyle.FontSize, you can get the best zoom result by using GcFontPickerZoomPolicy.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcFunctionKey
data.value: GcFunctionKeyZoomPolicy will change GcFunctionKey.Font and GcFunctionKey.Size when you zoom GcFunctionKey, so you can get the best zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcGroupBoxBase
data.value: Supports for the GcCheckedGroupBox, GcRadioGroupBoxChange and so on, if you change this type controls’s .CheckMarkSize, HorizontalSpace or VerticalSpace value, you’d better add GcGroupBoxControlPolicy to get a better zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcHeadingContainer
data.value: GcHeadingContainerZoomPolicy will change GcHeadingContainer.DesignSize and GcHeadingContainer.HeaderSettings.Font so that you can get the best zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcRadioButton
data.value: When you set GcRadioButton.CheckMarkAutoSize value is False and change GcRadioButton.CheckMarkSize value, you can get the best zoom result by using GcRadioButtonZoomPolicy.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcResizePanel
data.value: If GcResizePanel.ResizeMode is None, GcResizePanelZoomPolicy will give you a better zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcShapeButton
data.value: If you set GcShapeButton’s Default Image, Normal Image,Active Image, Hover Image or other Image properties, the image could not be zoomed, but the text will be zoomed by the font of parent. So GcShapeButtonZoomPolicy will keep GcShapeButton.Font.Size have no change so that you can get a better zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcSplitButton
data.value: If GcSplitButton.DropDownButtonWidth is not default value, you can get the best zoom result by using GcSplitButtonZoomPolicy.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcTabControl
data.value: When you set GcTabControl's TabsHeight, TabSpace, CloseButtonSize and other properties for layout, you can get the best zoom result by using GcRadioButtonZoomPolicy.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcTableLayoutContainer
data.value: If you set TableColumn.SizeType or TableRow.SizeType value is Absolute, add GcTableLayoutContainerPolicy can help you to get the best zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_PPK_GcTabPage
data.value: When you set the Font or ItemSize of GcTabControl's HotTrackStyle, SelectedStyle or TabStyle, you can get the best zoom result by using GcRadioButtonZoomPolicy.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_Spread
data.value: If the count of FpSpread.Sheets is bigger than 1, only current shown sheet can be zoomed, other sheets have no change, SpreadZoomPolicy can make all sheets can be zoomed no matter which sheet is current shown sheet.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_Strd_ComboBox
data.value: ComboBox will select all text when ComboBox.Font and ComboBox.Size change, ComboBoxZoomPolicy is used to disable this default behavior.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_Strd_DataGridView
data.value: MultiTouch Toolkit provides DataGridViewZoomPolicy to get a better zoom result for DataGridView. It can zoom the Size and Font for all Columns, Rows, or Cells.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_Strd_ListBox
data.value: ListBoxZoomPolicy ensure that ListBox.ColumnWidth value change when ListBox.MultiColumn is True and ListBox.CloumnWidth is bigger than 0.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_Strd_ListView
data.value: ListView.Font and ListView.Columns[i].Width will be changed while zooming because of MultiTouch Toolkit provides ListViewZoomPolicy.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_Strd_MonthCalendar
data.value: MonthCalendar.Font and MonthCalendar.Size always remain unchanged. MonthCanlendarZoomPolicy will move MonthCalendar to the center of the blank space.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_Strd_PictureBox
data.value: PictureBoxZoomPolicy makes PictureBox zoom result better when PictureBox.SizeMode isn’t Zoom and zoomfactor is bigger than 1f.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_Strd_SplitContainer
data.value: When you do zoom operation, SplitContainerZoomPolicy changes SplitContainer.SplitLineWidth and SplitContainer.SplitterDistance property value, so you can get the best zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_Strd_TableLayoutPanel
data.value: If TableLayoutPanel's ColumnStyle.SizeType or RowStyle.SizeType proeprty value is Absolute, change Size of TableLayoutPanel, ColumnStyle.Width and RowStyle.Height do not change. TableLayoutPanelZoomPolicy will help you change Column.Width and Row.Height in this case.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_Strd_TreeView
data.value: If TreeView’s following property value are not default value, change TreeView.Size or TreeView.Font do not cause these property value change. TreeViewZoomPolicy will help you change these value in this case.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_VisualBasicPowerPacks
data.value: Visual Basic Power Packs is a Visual Basic 6.0 compatibility feature provided by Microsoft. MultiTouch for Windows Forms provides VisualBasicPowerPacksZoomPolicy to support LineShape, OvalShape and RectangleShape’s zooming behavior.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_WPF_ElementHost
data.value: WPF Interoperability is a technology of using Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF) in a Windows Forms project. MultiTouch for Windows Forms provides WPF_ElementHostZoomPolicy to support ElementHost’s zooming behavior.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_Strd_FlowLayoutPanel
data.value: First, zoom in Form, then zoom out Form to 100%, controls’s layout maybe uncorrectly, FlowLayoutPanelZoomPolicy can make sure that controls’s layout correctly at any time.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_Strd_PropertyGrid
data.value: PropertyGrid’s bounds, font and layout’s zoom result may uncorrectly sometimes, PropertyGridZoomPolicy gives you a better zoom result.

data.name: ZoomPolicy_Strd_ToolStrip
data.value: By default, ToolStrip’s font can not zoom, ToolStripZoomPolicy can help you get the best zoom result.
